    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range xsd:boolean ;
    skos:definition """Indicates whether the contract is subject to a renewal clause.
WG Approval 09/11/2021 (epo:ContractTerm) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Is renewal indicator"@en .

epo:isSMESuitable a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Is s m e suitable"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The Lot is suitable for small and medium enterprises (SMEs).

Additional Information

This allows the buyer to make emphasis on the fact that the procedure has been designed having SMEs in mind. This indicator is also to be reflected in the selection criteria.

For example, number of employees and turnover are applicable to the definition of an SME.

WG Approval 15/10/2019
 (epo:ProcurementObject) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:ProcurementObject ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range xsd:boolean ;
    skos:definition """The Lot is suitable for small and medium enterprises (SMEs).

Additional Information

This allows the buyer to make emphasis on the fact that the procedure has been designed having SMEs in mind. This indicator is also to be reflected in the selection criteria.

For example, number of employees and turnover are applicable to the definition of an SME.

WG Approval 15/10/2019
 (epo:ProcurementObject) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Is s m e suitable"@en .

epo:isSubjectToGrouping rdfs:domain epo:Tender ;
    rdfs:range epo:LotGroup .

epo:isSubjectToProcedureSpecificTerm a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Is subject to procedure specific term"@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:Procedure ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range epo:ProcedureSpecificTerm ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf epo:isSubjectToTerm ;
    skos:prefLabel "Is subject to procedure specific term"@en .

epo:isSubmissionForAllLotsAllowed a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Is submission for all lots allowed"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """Indicates whether tenders may be submitted for all Lots.

Additional information:
This field is used to complement the SubmissionTerms (which are at the Lot level) for the Procedure level which is covered by the regulation (EU)-2015-1986 (modeled in the TED Standard Forms)

WG approval 23/08/2022
 (epo:ProcedureTerm) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:ProcedureTerm ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range xsd:boolean ;
    skos:definition """Indicates whether tenders may be submitted for all Lots.

Additional information:
This field is used to complement the SubmissionTerms (which are at the Lot level) for the Procedure level which is covered by the regulation (EU)-2015-1986 (modeled in the TED Standard Forms)

WG approval 23/08/2022
 (epo:ProcedureTerm) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Is submission for all lots allowed"@en .

epo:isSubmitedBy a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Is submited by"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """Relation indicating the submission of a tender by an economic operator.
WG approval 18/05/2021 (epo:Tender -> epo:Tenderer (+epo:isSubmitedBy)) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:Tender ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range epo:Tenderer ;
    skos:prefLabel "Is submited by"@en ;
    skos:scopeNote """Relation indicating the submission of a tender by an economic operator.
WG approval 18/05/2021 (epo:Tender -> epo:Tenderer (+epo:isSubmitedBy)) """@en .

epo:isSubmittedForLot a owl:FunctionalProperty,
        owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Is submitted for lot"@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:Tender ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range epo:Lot ;
    skos:prefLabel "Is submitted for lot"@en .

epo:isToBeRelaunched a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Is to be relaunched"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """Indicator of whether the procurement object is to be relaunched.

Additional information: 
This can be instantiated in the post award phase. 

This corresponds in eForms to BT-634  Procurement Relaunch.

WG Approval: 18/01/2022
 (epo:ProcurementProcessInformation) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:ProcurementProcessInformation ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range xsd:boolean ;
    skos:definition """Indicator of whether the procurement object is to be relaunched.

Additional information: 
This can be instantiated in the post award phase. 

This corresponds in eForms to BT-634  Procurement Relaunch.

WG Approval: 18/01/2022
 (epo:ProcurementProcessInformation) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Is to be relaunched"@en .

epo:isUsedForCandidateRestriction a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Is used for candidate restriction"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The criterion will be used to select the candidates to be invited for the second stage of a multistage procedure.

Additional Information:
This property is only used if a maximum number of candidates was foreseen in the procedure.
This corresponds in eForms to BT-40 Selection Criteria Second Stage Invite (epo:SelectionCriterion) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:SelectionCriterion ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range xsd:boolean ;
    skos:definition """The criterion will be used to select the candidates to be invited for the second stage of a multistage procedure.

Additional Information:
This property is only used if a maximum number of candidates was foreseen in the procedure.
This corresponds in eForms to BT-40 Selection Criteria Second Stage Invite (epo:SelectionCriterion) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Is used for candidate restriction"@en .

epo:isUsingEUFunds a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Is using e u funds"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The procurement foresees funding by the Europeanin Union funds such as the European Structural and Investment Funds or grants awarded by the European Union.

Additional Information:
The funding may cover the whole procurement or part of the procurement.
This corresponds in eForms to BT-60 EU Funds. This shall be interpreted in the context of BG-61 EU Funds (which can point to a group of Lots). (epo:ProcurementObject) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:ProcurementObject ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range xsd:boolean ;
    skos:definition """The procurement foresees funding by the Europeanin Union funds such as the European Structural and Investment Funds or grants awarded by the European Union.

Additional Information:
The funding may cover the whole procurement or part of the procurement.
This corresponds in eForms to BT-60 EU Funds. This shall be interpreted in the context of BG-61 EU Funds (which can point to a group of Lots). (epo:ProcurementObject) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Is using e u funds"@en .

epo:isVariant a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Is variant"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """Alternative solution to fulfil the buyer's needs as opposed to solutions indicated in the procurement documents.

Additional Information:

The permission to offer variants is only allowed if specified in a Contract Notice or a Prior Information Notice that used as a means for calling for a competition.
The buyer lays out minimum requirements in the procurement documents that must be respected by tenderers submitting variants.

WG Approval 29/05/2019

 (epo:Tender) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:Tender ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range xsd:boolean ;
    skos:definition """Alternative solution to fulfil the buyer's needs as opposed to solutions indicated in the procurement documents.

Additional Information:

The permission to offer variants is only allowed if specified in a Contract Notice or a Prior Information Notice that used as a means for calling for a competition.
The buyer lays out minimum requirements in the procurement documents that must be respected by tenderers submitting variants.

WG Approval 29/05/2019

 (epo:Tender) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Is variant"@en .

epo:isWithinFrameworkAgreement a owl:DatatypeProperty,
        owl:FunctionalProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Is within framework agreement"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """A contract resulting from the use of an existing framework agreement.

Additional information:
This corresponds in Eforms to BT-768 Contract Framework Agreement.
This indicator is generally used to differentiate the purchase contract within a framework agreement or a direct purchasing system. (epo:PurchaseContract) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:PurchaseContract ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range xsd:boolean ;
    skos:definition """A contract resulting from the use of an existing framework agreement.

Additional information:
This corresponds in Eforms to BT-768 Contract Framework Agreement.
This indicator is generally used to differentiate the purchase contract within a framework agreement or a direct purchasing system. (epo:PurchaseContract) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Is within framework agreement"@en .

epo:leadBy rdfs:domain epo:OrganisationGroup ;
    rdfs:range org:Organization .

epo:refersToNotice rdfs:domain epo:Notice ;
    rdfs:range epo:Notice .

epo:refersToPreviousNotice a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Refers to previous notice"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """
Additional information: 
This corresponds in eForms to BT-758 Change Notice Version Identifier. (epo:NoticeChange -> epo:Notice (+epo:refersToPreviousNotice)) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:NoticeChange ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range epo:Notice ;
    skos:definition """
Additional information: 
This corresponds in eForms to BT-758 Change Notice Version Identifier. (epo:NoticeChange -> epo:Notice (+epo:refersToPreviousNotice)) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Refers to previous notice"@en .

epo:refersToProcedure a owl:FunctionalProperty,
        owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Refers to procedure"@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:Notice ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range epo:Procedure ;
    skos:prefLabel "Refers to procedure"@en .

epo:setsGroupingContextForLot a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Sets grouping context for lot"@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:LotGroup ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range epo:Lot ;
    skos:prefLabel "Sets grouping context for lot"@en .

epo:substantiatesExclusionGround rdfs:domain epo:Tenderer ;
    rdfs:range epo:ExclusionGround .

epo:summarisesInformationForLotAwardOutcome a owl:FunctionalProperty,
        owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Summarises information for lot award outcome"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Relates to Lot submission. (epo:SubmissionStatisticalInformation -> epo:LotAwardOutcome (+epo:summarisesInformationForLotAwardOutcome)) "@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:SubmissionStatisticalInformation ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range epo:LotAwardOutcome ;
    skos:definition "Relates to Lot submission. (epo:SubmissionStatisticalInformation -> epo:LotAwardOutcome (+epo:summarisesInformationForLotAwardOutcome)) "@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Summarises information for lot award outcome"@en .

<http://data.europa.eu/m8g/Person> rdfs:subClassOf [ a owl:Restriction ;
            owl:maxCardinality 1 ;
            owl:onProperty epo:registeredAddress ] .

<http://data.europa.eu/m8g/description> a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Description"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """A short explanation supporting the understanding of the Requirement.        

Additional Information:
The explanation can include information about the nature, attributes, uses or any other additional information about the Requirement. (cccev:Requirement) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain <http://data.europa.eu/m8g/Requirement> ;
    rdfs:range rdfs:Literal ;
    skos:definition """A short explanation supporting the understanding of the Requirement.        

Additional Information:
The explanation can include information about the nature, attributes, uses or any other additional information about the Requirement. (cccev:Requirement) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Description"@en .

<http://data.europa.eu/m8g/email> a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Email"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "An electronic address through which the Contact Point can be contacted. (cpov:ContactPoint) "@en ;
    rdfs:domain <http://data.europa.eu/m8g/ContactPoint> ;
    rdfs:range rdfs:Literal ;
    skos:definition "An electronic address through which the Contact Point can be contacted. (cpov:ContactPoint) "@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Email"@en .

<http://data.europa.eu/m8g/name> a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Name"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Name of the Requirement. (cccev:Requirement) "@en ;
    rdfs:domain <http://data.europa.eu/m8g/Requirement> ;
    rdfs:range rdfs:Literal ;
    skos:definition "Name of the Requirement. (cccev:Requirement) "@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Name"@en .

<http://data.europa.eu/m8g/weight> a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Weight"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """Relative importance of the Criterion.

Additional Information:
The weight must be between 0 and 1. Usually, all Criteria can be integrated within a weighted sum equal to 1. (cccev:Criterion) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain <http://data.europa.eu/m8g/Criterion> ;
    rdfs:range xsd:decimal ;
    skos:definition """Relative importance of the Criterion.

Additional Information:
The weight must be between 0 and 1. Usually, all Criteria can be integrated within a weighted sum equal to 1. (cccev:Criterion) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Weight"@en .

time:numericDuration a owl:DatatypeProperty,
        owl:FunctionalProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Numeric duration"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Value of a temporal extent expressed as a number. (epo:SpecificDuration) "@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:SpecificDuration ;
    rdfs:range xsd:decimal ;
    skos:definition "Value of a temporal extent expressed as a number. (epo:SpecificDuration) "@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Numeric duration"@en .

<http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#addressArea> a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Address area"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The name or names of a geographic area or locality that groups a number of addressable objects for addressing purposes, without being an administrative unit.

Additional Information:
This would typically be part of a city, a neighbourhood or village, e.g. Montmartre. (locn:Address) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain <http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#Address> ;
    rdfs:range rdfs:Literal ;
    skos:definition """The name or names of a geographic area or locality that groups a number of addressable objects for addressing purposes, without being an administrative unit.

Additional Information:
This would typically be part of a city, a neighbourhood or village, e.g. Montmartre. (locn:Address) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Address area"@en .

<http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#adminUnitL1> rdfs:domain <http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#Address> .

<http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#adminUnitL2> rdfs:domain <http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#Address> .

<http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#fullAddress> a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Full address"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The complete address written as a formatted string.

Additional Information:
Use of this property is recommended as it will not suffer any misunderstandings that might arise through the breaking up of an address into its component parts. This property is analogous to vCard's label property but with two important differences: (1) formatting is not assumed so that, unlike vCard label, it may not be suitable to print this on an address label, (2) vCard's label property has a domain of vCard Address; the fullAddress property has no such restriction. An example of a full address is "Champ de Mars, 5 Avenue Anatole France, 75007 Paris, France". (locn:Address) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain <http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#Address> ;
    rdfs:range rdfs:Literal ;
    skos:definition """The complete address written as a formatted string.

Additional Information:
Use of this property is recommended as it will not suffer any misunderstandings that might arise through the breaking up of an address into its component parts. This property is analogous to vCard's label property but with two important differences: (1) formatting is not assumed so that, unlike vCard label, it may not be suitable to print this on an address label, (2) vCard's label property has a domain of vCard Address; the fullAddress property has no such restriction. An example of a full address is "Champ de Mars, 5 Avenue Anatole France, 75007 Paris, France". (locn:Address) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Full address"@en .

<http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#geographicName> rdfs:domain dct:Location .

<http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#locatorDesignator> rdfs:domain <http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#Address> .

<http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#locatorName> rdfs:domain <http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#Address> .

foaf:Person owl:disjointWith org:Organization .

epo:AwardDecision owl:disjointWith epo:Contract,
        epo:Tender .

epo:ContractLotCompletionInformation owl:disjointWith epo:LotAwardOutcome,
        epo:TenderAwardOutcome .

epo:EAuctionTechniqueUsage owl:disjointWith epo:DynamicPurchaseSystemTechniqueUsage,
        epo:FrameworkAgreementTechniqueUsage .

epo:ElementModificationDescription rdfs:subClassOf [ a owl:Restriction ;
            owl:maxCardinality 1 ;
            owl:onProperty epo:hasElementReference ] ;
    owl:disjointWith epo:ElementChangeDescription .

epo:EmploymentInformationProvider a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Employment information provider"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "A role of an agent responsible for providing information concerning the general regulatory framework for employment protection and working conditions."@en ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:subClassOf epo:AuxiliaryParty ;
    owl:disjointWith epo:EnvironmentalProtectionInformationProvider,
        epo:TaxInformationProvider ;
    skos:definition "A role of an agent responsible for providing information concerning the general regulatory framework for employment protection and working conditions."@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Employment information provider"@en .

epo:EnvironmentalProtectionInformationProvider a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Environmental protection information provider"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "A role of an agent responsible for providing information concerning the general regulatory framework for environmental protection."@en ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:subClassOf epo:AuxiliaryParty ;
    owl:disjointWith epo:EmploymentInformationProvider,
        epo:TaxInformationProvider ;
    skos:definition "A role of an agent responsible for providing information concerning the general regulatory framework for environmental protection."@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Environmental protection information provider"@en .

epo:ExpressionOfInterest owl:disjointWith epo:Notice,
        epo:ProcurementDocument .

epo:FrameworkAgreementTechniqueUsage a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Framework agreement technique usage"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """Technique that establishes the terms governing contracts to be awarded during a given period, in particular with regard to price and, where appropriate, the quantity envisaged.

WG approval 18/05/2021"""@en ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:subClassOf epo:TechniqueUsage ;
    owl:disjointWith epo:DynamicPurchaseSystemTechniqueUsage,
        epo:EAuctionTechniqueUsage ;
    skos:definition """Technique that establishes the terms governing contracts to be awarded during a given period, in particular with regard to price and, where appropriate, the quantity envisaged.

WG approval 18/05/2021"""@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Framework agreement technique usage"@en .

epo:LotGroupAwardInformation owl:disjointWith epo:LotAwardOutcome,
        epo:TenderAwardOutcome .

epo:NoticeDescription rdfs:subClassOf [ a owl:Restriction ;
            owl:cardinality 1 ;
            owl:onProperty epo:describesNotice ] .

epo:RequestForClarification owl:disjointWith epo:Notice,
        epo:ProcurementDocument .

epo:RequestForParticipation owl:disjointWith epo:Notice,
        epo:ProcurementDocument .

epo:ReviewIrregularitySummary owl:disjointWith epo:ReviewRequestSummary,
        epo:SubmissionStatisticalInformation .

epo:SubcontractTerm rdfs:subClassOf epo:ContractSpecificTerm ;
    owl:disjointWith epo:ContractTerm .

epo:System owl:disjointWith org:Organization .

epo:TaxInformationProvider a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Tax information provider"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "A role of an agent responsible for providing information concerning the general regulatory framework for taxes."@en ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:subClassOf epo:AuxiliaryParty ;
    owl:disjointWith epo:EmploymentInformationProvider,
        epo:EnvironmentalProtectionInformationProvider ;
    skos:definition "A role of an agent responsible for providing information concerning the general regulatory framework for taxes."@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Tax information provider"@en .

epo:address rdfs:domain [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:unionOf ( <http://data.europa.eu/m8g/ContactPoint> org:Organization ) ],
        dct:Location ;
    rdfs:range [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:unionOf ( <http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#Address> ) ],
        <http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#Address> .

epo:hasElementReference a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Has element reference"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """Reference to the class instance in the current notice.

Additional information: 
This corresponds in eForms to BT-13716 Change Previous Notice Section Identifier, BT-786     Review Notice Section Identifier and BT-1501     Modification Previous Notice Section Identifier. (epo:ElementChangeDescription) Reference to the class instance in the current notice.

Additional information: 
This corresponds in eForms to BT-13716 Change Previous Notice Section Identifier, BT-786     Review Notice Section Identifier and BT-1501     Modification Previous Notice Section Identifier.
 (epo:ElementModificationDescription) Reference to the class instance in the current notice.

Additional information: 
This corresponds in eForms to BT-13716 Change Previous Notice Section Identifier, BT-786     Review Notice Section Identifier and BT-1501     Modification Previous Notice Section Identifier. (epo:ReviewObject) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:unionOf ( epo:ElementChangeDescription epo:ElementModificationDescription epo:ReviewObject ) ] ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range xsd:anyURI ;
    skos:definition """Reference to the class instance in the current notice.

Additional information: 
This corresponds in eForms to BT-13716 Change Previous Notice Section Identifier, BT-786     Review Notice Section Identifier and BT-1501     Modification Previous Notice Section Identifier. (epo:ElementChangeDescription) Reference to the class instance in the current notice.

Additional information: 
This corresponds in eForms to BT-13716 Change Previous Notice Section Identifier, BT-786     Review Notice Section Identifier and BT-1501     Modification Previous Notice Section Identifier.
 (epo:ElementModificationDescription) Reference to the class instance in the current notice.

Additional information: 
This corresponds in eForms to BT-13716 Change Previous Notice Section Identifier, BT-786     Review Notice Section Identifier and BT-1501     Modification Previous Notice Section Identifier. (epo:ReviewObject) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Has element reference"@en .

epo:hasEstimatedValue a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Has estimated value"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """A forecast of the value of the procurement before competition.

Additional Information:
Different cases of estimated values may refer to a lot, the global value of the procedure, or of a combinatorial value of a group of lots.
The forecast is calculated by the buyer and covers all revenues  whether coming from the buyer or third parties.
See for example recital (19), Article 5 of Directive 2014/24/EU and other articles from the rest of Directives about procurement.

In the case of framework agreements and dynamic purchasing systems this refers to the maximum estimated value.

This property corresponds to BT-27 in eForms (for Lot and Procedure) and can be used for BT-157 (for LotGroup).
<b>
</b><b>WG Approval 05/12/2019</b>

 (epo:ProcurementObject -> epo:MonetaryValue (+epo:hasEstimatedValue)) A forecast of the value of the procurement before competition.

Additional Information
Different cases of estimated values may refer to a lot, the global value of the procedure, or of a combinatorial value of a group of lots.
The forecast is calculated by the buyer and covers all revenues  whether coming from the buyer or third parties.
See for example recital (19), Article 5 of Directive 2014/24/EU and other articles from the rest of Directives about procurement.

In the case of lots or groups of lots using framework agreements and dynamic purchasing systems this refers to the maximum estimated value.
<b>
</b>This property corresponds to BT-27 in eForms (for Lot and Procedure) and can be used for BT-157 (for LotGroup).
<b>
</b><b>WG Approval 05/12/2019</b> (epo:LotGroup -> epo:MonetaryValue (+epo:hasEstimatedValue)) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:unionOf ( epo:ProcurementObject epo:LotGroup ) ] ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:unionOf ( epo:MonetaryValue ) ] ;
    skos:definition """A forecast of the value of the procurement before competition.

Additional Information:
Different cases of estimated values may refer to a lot, the global value of the procedure, or of a combinatorial value of a group of lots.
The forecast is calculated by the buyer and covers all revenues  whether coming from the buyer or third parties.
See for example recital (19), Article 5 of Directive 2014/24/EU and other articles from the rest of Directives about procurement.

In the case of framework agreements and dynamic purchasing systems this refers to the maximum estimated value.

This property corresponds to BT-27 in eForms (for Lot and Procedure) and can be used for BT-157 (for LotGroup).
<b>
</b><b>WG Approval 05/12/2019</b>

 (epo:ProcurementObject -> epo:MonetaryValue (+epo:hasEstimatedValue)) A forecast of the value of the procurement before competition.

Additional Information
Different cases of estimated values may refer to a lot, the global value of the procedure, or of a combinatorial value of a group of lots.
The forecast is calculated by the buyer and covers all revenues  whether coming from the buyer or third parties.
See for example recital (19), Article 5 of Directive 2014/24/EU and other articles from the rest of Directives about procurement.

In the case of lots or groups of lots using framework agreements and dynamic purchasing systems this refers to the maximum estimated value.
<b>
</b>This property corresponds to BT-27 in eForms (for Lot and Procedure) and can be used for BT-157 (for LotGroup).
<b>
</b><b>WG Approval 05/12/2019</b> (epo:LotGroup -> epo:MonetaryValue (+epo:hasEstimatedValue)) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Has estimated value"@en .

epo:hasURL a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Has u r l"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The identifier of a resource.

Additional Information

For example:

1. The URL of the system from where to access the procurement documents;
2. The URL of the system for the submission of tender documents;
3. The URL of the system from where to download a tool to communicate with the Buyer;
4. The URL of the system used by a Technique to allow Economic Operators to exchange information with the Buyer (e.g. eAuction and DPS Systems)
5. The URL of the system used to exchange information between Buyer and EO for questions and clarifications;

WG Approval 30/09/2019

 (cv:Channel) The identifier of a resource.

Additional Information

For example:

1. The URL of the system from where to access the procurement documents;
2. The URL of the system for the submission of tender documents;
3. The URL of the system from where to download a tool to communicate with the Buyer;
4. The URL of the system used by a Technique to allow Economic Operators to exchange information with the Buyer (e.g. eAuction and DPS Systems)
5. The URL of the system used to exchange information between Buyer and EO for questions and clarifications;

WG Approval 30/09/2019 (epo:Fund) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:unionOf ( <http://data.europa.eu/m8g/Channel> epo:Fund ) ] ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range xsd:anyURI ;
    skos:definition """The identifier of a resource.

Additional Information

For example:

1. The URL of the system from where to access the procurement documents;
2. The URL of the system for the submission of tender documents;
3. The URL of the system from where to download a tool to communicate with the Buyer;
4. The URL of the system used by a Technique to allow Economic Operators to exchange information with the Buyer (e.g. eAuction and DPS Systems)
5. The URL of the system used to exchange information between Buyer and EO for questions and clarifications;

WG Approval 30/09/2019

 (cv:Channel) The identifier of a resource.

Additional Information

For example:

1. The URL of the system from where to access the procurement documents;
2. The URL of the system for the submission of tender documents;
3. The URL of the system from where to download a tool to communicate with the Buyer;
4. The URL of the system used by a Technique to allow Economic Operators to exchange information with the Buyer (e.g. eAuction and DPS Systems)
5. The URL of the system used to exchange information between Buyer and EO for questions and clarifications;

WG Approval 30/09/2019 (epo:Fund) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Has u r l"@en .

epo:hasValidityPeriod a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Has validity period"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The property indicating when the ItemCertificate is in force.

WG approval 26/07/2022 (epo-cat:ItemCertificate -> epo:Period (+epo:hasValidityPeriod)) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:unionOf ( epo:SubmissionTerm epo:TechniqueUsage epo:ItemCertificate epo:Order epo:Catalogue ) ] ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:unionOf ( epo:Period ) ] ;
    skos:definition """The property indicating when the ItemCertificate is in force.

WG approval 26/07/2022 (epo-cat:ItemCertificate -> epo:Period (+epo:hasValidityPeriod)) """@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Has validity period"@en .

epo:isSubjectToTerm a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Is subject to term"@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:ProcurementObject ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range epo:Term ;
    skos:prefLabel "Is subject to term"@en .

epo:playedBy a owl:FunctionalProperty,
        owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Played by"@en ;
    rdfs:domain epo:AgentInRole ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range foaf:Agent ;
    skos:prefLabel "Played by"@en .

epo:registeredAddress a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Registered address"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The registered address relationship links a Resource with the legally registered Address.

Additional Information:
It is the address to which formal communications can be sent, such as the postal address.
 (org:Organization -> locn:Address (+cv:registeredAddress)) """@en,
        """The registered address relationship links a Resource with the legally registered Address.

Additional Information:
It is the address to which formal communications can be sent, such as the postal address. (cpv:Person -> locn:Address (+legal:registeredAddress)) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain <http://data.europa.eu/m8g/Person>,
        org:Organization ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range <http://www.w3.org/ns/locn#Address> ;
    skos:prefLabel "Registered address"@en ;
    skos:scopeNote """The registered address relationship links a Resource with the legally registered Address.

Additional Information:
It is the address to which formal communications can be sent, such as the postal address.
 (org:Organization -> locn:Address (+cv:registeredAddress)) """@en,
        """The registered address relationship links a Resource with the legally registered Address.

Additional Information:
It is the address to which formal communications can be sent, such as the postal address. (cpv:Person -> locn:Address (+legal:registeredAddress)) """@en .

<http://data.europa.eu/m8g/Criterion> rdfs:subClassOf [ a owl:Restriction ;
            owl:maxCardinality 1 ;
            owl:onProperty <http://data.europa.eu/m8g/weight> ] ;
    owl:disjointWith <http://data.europa.eu/m8g/Constraint> .

<http://data.europa.eu/m8g/PublicOrganisation> rdfs:subClassOf org:Organization ;
    owl:disjointWith epo:Business,
        epo:OrganisationGroup .

epo:AuxiliaryParty rdfs:subClassOf epo:AgentInRole .

epo:CatalogueProvider owl:disjointWith epo:Contractor,
        epo:Tenderer,
        epo:Winner .

epo:DynamicPurchaseSystemTechniqueUsage a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Dynamic purchase system technique usage"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """An electronic system that is set up by a procuring entity which lists the economic operators that satisfy the selection and exclusion criteria.   This technique then allows the purchase via consultation of the listed tenderers using award criteria.

(WG approval 13/07/2018)"""@en ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:subClassOf epo:TechniqueUsage ;
    owl:disjointWith epo:EAuctionTechniqueUsage,
        epo:FrameworkAgreementTechniqueUsage ;
    skos:definition """An electronic system that is set up by a procuring entity which lists the economic operators that satisfy the selection and exclusion criteria.   This technique then allows the purchase via consultation of the listed tenderers using award criteria.

(WG approval 13/07/2018)"""@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Dynamic purchase system technique usage"@en .

epo:InnovativeProcurement rdfs:subClassOf epo:StrategicProcurement ;
    owl:disjointWith epo:GreenProcurement,
        epo:SocialProcurement .

epo:OfferingParty rdfs:subClassOf epo:AgentInRole .

epo:OtherEntity owl:disjointWith epo:Contractor,
        epo:Tenderer,
        epo:Winner .

epo:PlannedProcurementPart owl:disjointWith epo:Lot,
        epo:Procedure .

epo:ReviewObject owl:disjointWith epo:Contract,
        epo:Tender .

epo:ReviewRequester owl:disjointWith epo:Contractor,
        epo:Tenderer,
        epo:Winner .

epo:SocialProcurement a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Social procurement"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """An instance of the class SocialProcurement  is represented in eForms with the code "soc-obj" defined in the codelist strategic-procurement.


Research (21/01/2020): 
Socially responsible public procurement (SRPP):

‘SRPP’ means procurement operations that take into account one or more of the following social considerations: employment opportunities, decent work, compliance with social and labour rights, social inclusion (including persons with disabilities), equal opportunities, accessibility design for all, taking account of sustainability criteria, including ethical trade issues and wider voluntary compliance with corporate social responsibility (CSR), while observing the principles enshrined in the Treaty for the European Union (TFEU) and the Procurement Directives. 
Source: Buying Social - A Guide to Taking Account of Social Considerations in Public Procurement (Publications Office of the European Union, 2011) https://op.europa.eu/en/publication-detail/-/publication/cb70c481-0e29-4040-9be2-c408cddf081f/language-en
See Article 18 and Annex X Directive 2014/24."""@en ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:subClassOf epo:StrategicProcurement ;
    owl:disjointWith epo:GreenProcurement,
        epo:InnovativeProcurement ;
    skos:definition """An instance of the class SocialProcurement  is represented in eForms with the code "soc-obj" defined in the codelist strategic-procurement.


Research (21/01/2020): 
Socially responsible public procurement (SRPP):

‘SRPP’ means procurement operations that take into account one or more of the following social considerations: employment opportunities, decent work, compliance with social and labour rights, social inclusion (including persons with disabilities), equal opportunities, accessibility design for all, taking account of sustainability criteria, including ethical trade issues and wider voluntary compliance with corporate social responsibility (CSR), while observing the principles enshrined in the Treaty for the European Union (TFEU) and the Procurement Directives. 
Source: Buying Social - A Guide to Taking Account of Social Considerations in Public Procurement (Publications Office of the European Union, 2011) https://op.europa.eu/en/publication-detail/-/publication/cb70c481-0e29-4040-9be2-c408cddf081f/language-en
See Article 18 and Annex X Directive 2014/24."""@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Social procurement"@en .

epo:SpecificDuration a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Specific duration"@en ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:subClassOf [ a owl:Restriction ;
            owl:cardinality 1 ;
            owl:onProperty time:numericDuration ],
        epo:Duration ;
    owl:disjointWith epo:IndefiniteDuration ;
    skos:prefLabel "Specific duration"@en .

epo:Subcontractor owl:disjointWith epo:Contractor,
        epo:Tenderer,
        epo:Winner .

epo:dependsOnBuyer rdfs:domain [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:unionOf ( epo:Awarder epo:BudgetProvider epo:ParticipationRequestProcessor epo:ParticipationRequestReceiver epo:TenderProcessor epo:TenderReceiver epo:PaymentExecutor ) ] ;
    rdfs:range [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:unionOf ( epo:Buyer ) ] .

epo:dependsOnServiceProvider rdfs:domain [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:unionOf ( epo:BudgetProvider epo:ParticipationRequestProcessor epo:ParticipationRequestReceiver epo:PaymentExecutor epo:TenderProcessor epo:TenderReceiver ) ] ;
    rdfs:range [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:unionOf ( epo:ProcurementServiceProvider ) ] .

epo:hasID a owl:FunctionalProperty,
        owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Has i d"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """A unique identifier of the instance of the concept.
Additional Information:
For example, in the case of the Procurement Identifier, this could be the European Public Procurement Identifier, and/or any other identifier provided by the buyer, the service provider or any other stakeholder.
WG Approval 12/11/2019

 (cccev:InformationConcept -> epo:Identifier (+epo:hasID)) A unique identifier of the instance of the concept.

Additional Information

For example, in the case of the Procurement Identifier, this could be the European Public Procurement Identifier, and/or any other identifier provided by the buyer, the service provider or any other stakeholder.

WG Approval 12/11/2019
 (epo:Document -> epo:Identifier (+epo:hasID)) A unique identifier of the instance of the concept.

Additional Information

For example, in the case of the Procurement Identifier, this could be the European Public Procurement Identifier, and/or any other identifier provided by the buyer, the service provider or any other stakeholder.

WG Approval 12/11/2019
 (epo:Fund -> epo:Identifier (+epo:hasID)) A unique identifier of the instance of the concept.
Additional Information:
For example, in the case of the Procurement Identifier, this could be the European Public Procurement Identifier, and/or any other identifier provided by the buyer, the service provider or any other stakeholder.
WG Approval 12/11/2019
 (foaf:Agent -> epo:Identifier (+epo:hasID)) A unique identifier of the instance of the concept.

Additional Information

For example, in the case of the Procurement Identifier, this could be the European Public Procurement Identifier, and/or any other identifier provided by the buyer, the service provider or any other stakeholder.

WG Approval 12/11/2019
 (epo:ProcurementObject -> epo:Identifier (+epo:hasID)) A unique identifier of the instance of the concept.

Additional Information

For example, in the case of the Procurement Identifier, this could be the European Public Procurement Identifier, and/or any other identifier provided by the buyer, the service provider or any other stakeholder.

WG Approval 12/11/2019
 (epo-cat:CatalogueLine -> epo:Identifier (+epo:hasID)) A unique identifier of the instance of the concept.

Additional Information

For example, in the case of the Procurement Identifier, this could be the European Public Procurement Identifier, and/or any other identifier provided by the buyer, the service provider or any other stakeholder.

WG Approval 12/11/2019 (epo-cat:Batch -> epo:Identifier (+epo:hasID)) """@en ;
    rdfs:domain [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:unionOf ( <http://data.europa.eu/m8g/InformationConcept> epo:Document epo:Fund foaf:Agent epo:ProcurementObject epo:CatalogueLine epo:Batch ) ] ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://data.europa.eu/a4g/ontology> ;
    rdfs:range [ a owl:Class ;
            owl:unionOf ( epo:Identifier ) ] ;
    skos:definition """A unique identifier of the instance of the concept.
Additional Information:
For example, in the case of the Procurement Identifier, this could be the European Public Procurement Identifier, and/or any other identifier provided by the buyer, the service provider or any other stakeholder.
WG Approval 12/11/2019

 (cccev:InformationConcept -> epo:Identifier (+epo:hasID)) A unique identifier of the instance of the concept.

Additional Information

For example, in the case of the Procurement Identifier, this could be the European Public Procurement Identifier, and/or any other identifier provided by the buyer, the service provider or any other stakeholder.

WG Approval 12/11/2019
 (epo:Document -> epo:Identifier (+epo:hasID)) A unique identifier of the instance of the concept.

Additional Information

For example, in the case of the Procurement Identifier, this could be the European Public Procurement Identifier, and/or any other identifier provided by the buyer, the service provider or any other stakeholder.

WG Approval 12/11/2019
 (epo:Fund -> epo:Identifier (+epo:hasID)) A unique identifier of the instance of the concept.
Additional Information:
For example, in the case of the Procurement Identifier, this could be the European Public Procurement Identifier, and/or any other identifier provided by the buyer, the service provider or any other stakeholder.
WG Approval 12/11/2019
 (foaf:Agent -> epo:Identifier (+epo:hasID)) A unique identifier of the instance of the concept.

Additional Information

For example, in the case of the Procurement Identifier, this could be the European Public Procurement Identifier, and/or any other identifier provided by the buyer, the service provider or any other stakeholder.

